Description: Fragment of lip, neck and double handle of a Koan pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay medium light red- brown; blue-grey core; some mica. Rectangular stamp with club symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 66. Name Antiphilos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0095)
